ğŸ“Œ Overview

Today I learned about Docker Compose, a tool used to manage multi-container applications. It allows multiple services like web servers, databases, and caches to run together using a single configuration file called docker-compose.yml.

Docker Compose simplifies container orchestration, improves consistency, and reduces manual configuration.

ğŸ³ What is Docker Compose?

Docker Compose allows you to define and manage multiple containers as a single application using a YAML configuration file.

âœ… Benefits

Simplified multi-container management

Single configuration file

Easy orchestration

Consistent development and production environments

ğŸ“„ Docker Compose Configuration File
âœ… File Name
docker-compose.yml

ğŸ§± Key Components
version

Defines Compose file syntax version.

services

Defines containers required for the application.

image

Specifies Docker image for the service.

ports

Maps container ports to host ports.

environment

Defines environment variables inside container.

ğŸ§ª Example Compose File
version: '3'

services:
  web:
    image: nginx
    ports:
      - "8080:80"

  db:
    image: mysql
    environment:
      MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD: abcd1234

â–¶ï¸ Running Docker Compose Services
âœ… Command
docker compose up

ğŸ“– Description

Starts all services defined in the Compose file. It pulls images, creates containers, networks, and starts services.

ğŸ’¡ Use Cases

Running full application stack

Local development setup

Microservices deployment

ğŸ“Š Viewing Running Services
âœ… Command
docker compose ps

ğŸ“– Description

Shows running services with status and container details.

âœ… Command
docker compose ps -a

ğŸ“– Description

Shows all services including stopped ones.

ğŸ” Viewing Container Details
âœ… Command
docker ps

ğŸ“– Description

Displays running containers with detailed container-level information.

ğŸš€ Key Learnings

Docker Compose simplifies multi-container application setup.

docker-compose.yml defines service configuration.

Compose automatically creates containers and networks.

Helps maintain consistent environments across development and production.